    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static DatabaseCfg create(PropertiesCfg cfg)
        Retrieve keys and values from a database table and make them available as a normal configuration object Access is done leveraging the JDBC infrastructure from Integration Server. For that purpose, if so configured by specifying the property "jdbc.alias", aliases (pool and functional) will be created with this value. Alternatively, an existing functional alias can be specified with the property "jdbc.functionalAlias". The latter will than be used directly and no aliases are created or updated.
        Parameters:
        cfg - Configuration holding the properties for database access
        Returns:
        database configuration
